body:
It appears that if a module has a port which is an unpacked array with only one element in it, then you get a "failed to elaborate port expression" error.

For example:
```SystemVerilog
module SimpleLAPassthrough(
input logic [7:0] laIn [0:0],
output logic [7:0] laOut [0:0]
);
assign laOut[0] = laIn[0];
endmodule : SimpleLAPassthrough
module tb;
logic  [7:0] laIn[0:0];
logic  [7:0] laOut[0:0];
SimpleLAPassthrough dut(.laIn(laIn), .laOut(laOut));
endmodule : tb
```

Gives errors like this:
```
tmp_test/tmp_test371651767.sv:16: error: Array laIn needs an array index here.
tmp_test/tmp_test371651767.sv:16: error: Failed to elaborate port expression.
tmp_test/tmp_test371651767.sv:16: assert: elaborate.cc:1649: failed assertion prts[0]->unpacked_dimensions()==0
Aborted
```

This was run on iverilog "Version 11.0 (stable)"

